HEADWORD: Disquietal
<hw>Dis*qui"et*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
disquieting; a state of disquiet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[It] roars and strives 'gainst its <qex>disquietal</qex>.</q>
